The paper discusses the limitations of RDF in representing contextual information, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed solution involves graph similarity, which is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also touches on the construction of knowledge structures, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
